N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 22 ยง 137.10 - Confidentiality

State Regulations

All proceedings and hearings commenced and
conducted in accordance with this Part, including all papers in the arbitration
case file, shall be confidential, except to the extent necessary to take
ancillary legal action with respect to a fee matter. Notes
